{"cursor":"4435","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nA 'job' is a regular activity performed in exchange for payment. A person\nusually begins a job by becoming an employee, volunteering, or starting a\nbusiness. The duration of a job may range from an hour (in the case of odd jobs)\nto a lifetime (in the case of some judges). If a person is trained for a certain\ntype of job, they may have a profession. The series of jobs a person holds in\ntheir life is their career.\n","linknr":428,"url":"Job_(role)","recorded":1362584784,"links":30,"instances":["biblical_figure"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Employment"],"headings":["Jobs for people","Job opening","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Merge-arrow.svg/50px-Merge-arrow.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f8/Wiktionary-logo-en.svg/37px-Wiktionary-logo-en.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["job","biblical_figure"]],"members":["job"],"related":["Money","Employee","Volunteer","Business","Lifetime_employment","Judge","Profession","Career","Student","Disabled","Retired","Full_time","Part_time","Temporary_work","Odd_jobs","Seasonal_jobs","Self-employment","Training","Academic_degree","Odd_job","Unemployed","Vocation","Actress","Professional_athlete","Laborer","Semi-professional","Wright_brothers","Rite_of_passage","Culture","Housekeeping","Odd_job","Family_business","Summer_vacation","Higher_education","Internship","Resume","Employer","Job_interview","Conceptual_metaphor","Real_estate","Intellectual_rights","Intellectual_property","Online_Etymology_Dictionary","Job_(Biblical_figure)","Folk_etymology","Economics","Business","Wage_labor","Employ